{'title': 'Siamese architecture', 'comment': 'Thanks for the comment.

- The input to each branch of our Siamese architecture is a one-hot encoding of a word from the vocabulary. Next, each of the branches goes through a fully-connected linear layer, followed by the point cloud layer, which is a fully-connected linear layer whose output is normalized to lie within the unit ball. The Sinkhorn distance is then applied to the outputs of the two branches to compute the distances used within the contrastive loss.

